          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1705422658161-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the curry is ready, remove the dish from the oven and stir through your<strong> natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Leave to stand for 5 min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop) – this is your <strong>baked</strong> <strong>chicken & almond curry</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a toaster for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1705422664793-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1705422664793-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1705422664793-x700.jpg",
